
[1]acacia

   ACA'CIA, n. [L. acacia, a thorn, from Gr., a point.]

   Egyptian thorn, a species of plant ranked by Linne under the genus
   mimosa, and by others, made a distinct genus. Of the flowers of one
   species, the Chinese make a yellow dye which bears washing in silks,
   and appears with elegance on paper.
